Defendant Rodney L Clark in court, in custody, with attorney Paul S. Crawford.   Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to Count 1.  Count 2 is dismissed and read-in.  Court finds defendant guilty.    The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE:

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR.  Transfer is allowed to Milwaukee County.  

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with Wal Mart
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  $273.96 to WalMart on this case (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);
                         $150.52 to WalMart on case 16CM23 (dismissed and read-in)

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

DRGOD:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
